Gift to Kim Jong Il from Speaker of House of Representatives of Philippines  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by Speaker of the House of Representatives of the Philippines Jose de Venecia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was conveyed by the speaker on July 30 to Pak Ui Chun, minister of Foreign Affairs, who is leading a DPRK delegation on a visit to the Philippines.

Talks between Kim Yong Nam and Ethiopian PM Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addis Ababa, July 30 (KCNA Correspondent) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, held talks with Meles Zenawi, prime minister of Ethiopia, in Addis Ababa on July 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on the issue of boosting the friendly relations between the two countries and issues of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Minister of Public Health Choe Chang Sik, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Hyong Jun, Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade Ri Myong San and DPRK Ambassador to Ethiopia O Ul Rok. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there were Asfaw Dingamo, minister of Water Resources, Mahdi Ahmed, director general for Asia, Oceania and Middle East of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Kim visited the Ethiopian National Museum here on July 29. On July 28 he planted a tree in the compound of the Presidential Palace on the occasion of the "year of the Millennium in Ethiopia" before visiting the museum of the palace.

Inter-Sector Talks between DPRK and Ethiopia Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addis Ababa, July 30 (KCNA Correspondent) -- Inter-sector talks between the DPRK and the Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia were held in Addis Ababa on July 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks were held separately between Minister of Public Health Choe Chang Sik of the DPRK and Minister of Health Tewodros Adehanom, and between Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Hyong Jun and Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Tekeda Alemu and between Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade Ri Myong San and Minister of State for Trade and Industry Ahmed Tusa of Ethiopia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on the issue of boosting the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries in different fields as desired by the two peoples and matters of mutual concern.

Message of Thanks to Ethiopian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Tuesday sent a message of thanks to Girma Wolde-Giorgis, President of Ethiopia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon leaving your Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia after successfully winding up my visit to it, I express deep thanks to Your Excellency and your friendly government and people for the cordial hospitality accorded to us. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At a series of talks and conversations we had this time we had an exhaustive exchange of views on the issue of boosting the bilateral relations and matters of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is my belief that our visit to your country that took place under the deep care of Your Excellency and your leadership would mark an important occasion in putting the traditional friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries on a higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Availing myself of this opportunity, I would like to sincerely wish Your Excellency good health and happiness and your friendly people fresh progress and prosperity.

Kim Yong Nam Leaves Addis Ababa 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addis Ababa, July 31 (KCNA Correspondent) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Tuesday left Addis Ababa after winding up his official goodwill visit to Ethiopia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam and his party were seen off at the airport by officials concerned including the director general of Protocol of the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry, the DPRK ambassador to Ethiopia and embassy officials.

Talks between DPRK Foreign Minister and Philippine Secretary of Foreign Affairs Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Talks between DPRK Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun and Philippine Secretary of Foreign Affairs Alberto Gatmaitan Romulo were held at the International Conference Center in Manila on July 29. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were members of the DPRK delegation and from the Philippine side the deputy-secretary of Foreign Affairs and other officials concerned and the Philippine ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day the DPRK foreign minister paid a courtesy call on Speaker of the House of Representatives Jose de Venecia and was feted by the Philippine secretary of Foreign Affairs.

Agreement between DPRK and Philippine Foreign Ministries Inked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- An agreement on establishing the bilateral negotiating system between the DPRK foreign ministry and the Philippine foreign ministry was signed in Manila on July 29. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the signing ceremony from the DPRK side were members of the DPRK delegation headed by Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun and from the Philippine side Philippine Secretary of Foreign Affairs Alberto Gatmaitan Romulo and officials concerned and the Philippine ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The agreement was inked by the foreign ministers of the two countries.

Wreaths Laid before Statue and Grave of Kang Pan Sok 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the statue of Kang Pan Sok, an indomitable revolutionary fighter and outstanding leader of the Korean women's movement, at the Chilgol Revolutionary Site and her grave in Mangyongdae on Tuesday on the occasion of the 75th anniversary of her demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen before her statue and grave were wreaths sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremonies were Choe Thae Bok, Choe Yong Rim and officials of the party and armed forces organs and power bodies, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons of the KPA and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Placed before the statue and grave of Kang Pan Sok were wreaths in the name of the WPK Central Committee, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the Cabinet of the DPRK, working people's organizations, ministries, national institutions and educational, public health and media institutions, revolutionary schools and party and power organs and farms in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid silent tribute to her, recollecting her revolutionary life.

Kang Pan Sok's Life Will Shine long along with Songun Revolutionary Exploits
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- July 31 this year is the 75th anniversary of the death of Kang Pan Sok (mother of President Kim Il Sung), an outstanding leader of the Korean women's emancipation movement and indomitable revolutionary fighter. On this occasion, the Korean people are looking back with deep emotion upon her brilliant life which was dedicated to the cause of building the Juche-oriented army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Firmly convinced that only Songun was the way for the liberation of the country and the freedom and happiness of the people, she exerted all her efforts to uphold President Kim Il Sung's idea of attaching importance to arms at the dawn of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She handed over to her son two pistols left by his father Kim Hyong Jik. The pistols were associated with the father's firm will that the country should be won back without fail generation after generation. She devoted herself to implementing the President's line on armed struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She organized and mobilized members of the anti-Japanese women's association to secure military uniforms, shoes, supplies and others for the Anti-Japanese People's Guerilla Army and looked after the lodging and boarding of the youth people who came from various areas to fight with arms in their hands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seeing the reliable figures of guerillas just after the foundation of the first Juche-oriented revolutionary armed force of the Korean people and stroking this or that rifle, she said in earnest: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "I am proud of you. Now we have our own army! That's what we needed. You must destroy the Japanese and win back the country without fail." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the expedition to south Manchuria, the President came home to inquire after his sick mother. She, with the lofty intention, did not scruple to send him to the Songun revolutionary struggle, saying that a man with the determination to win back the ruined country should think of the country and people above the apprehension for household affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President had kept the lofty image of the upright mother on the day in his mind as one of a teacher. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President, always remembering the words and last image of his mother, accomplished the historic cause of national liberation through the protracted bloody anti-Japanese war and built a powerful socialist country, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defense.

Greetings to Swiss President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Micheline Calmy - Rey, Swiss President, on the occasion of the national day of Switzerland on July 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would grow stronger in the mutual interests, the message wished the Swiss president success in his work.

Greetings to President of Benin
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Thomas Boni Yayi, President of Benin, on July 28 on the occasion of the 47th anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in the message expressed belief that the traditional relations of friendship and cooperation between the DPRK and Benin would grow stronger in the interests of the two peoples and sincerely wished the president big success in his work for the development of the country.

22nd Songdowon International Children's Camping Starts
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Wonsan, July 30 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of receiving the 22nd batch of Songdowon international children campers took place on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were camping groups of Russia, China, Mongolia, Tanzania and Poland and camping group of Korean schoolchildren. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants laid floral baskets and bouquets before the statue of President Kim Il Sung at the camp before paying tribute to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After a clarion call was sounded, the camping flag was hoisted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony a congratulatory speech was followed by a report and speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this camping period campers from various countries together with Korean children will have the opportunity to train their bodies and minds and deepen the friendship through diverse activities including swimming, mountaineering, art and sporting activities and games and amusement activities and the operation of "national days."

Day of Korean People's Victory in War Observed in Britain
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of Songun Policy posted a special write-up entitled "Day of Great Victory-July 27" on the Internet homepage on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of the victory of the Korean people in the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage posted photographs of President Kim Il Sung who led the Fatherland Liberation War to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage in the article recalled that the U.S. imperialists launched an armed invasion against the DPRK on June 25, 1950 with an aim to realize their ambition for world domination and mobilized huge armed forces and war hardware for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people defeated the U.S. imperialist aggressors and reliably protected the dignity and honor of the country by displaying unrivalled self-sacrificing spirit and popular heroism, the homepage noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage cited facts to prove the U.S. imperialists' loss in the Korean war, stressing that the President's Juche-based line of building the army and outstanding leadership were a decisive factor of the victory in the war.

Kim Jong Il Praised by Head of Russian Dancing Troupe 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il is not only the great leader but genius of literature and art. Mira Koltsova, head of the State Academy Beryozka Dancing Troupe of Russia Named after N. S. Nadezhdina, said this when interviewed by KCNA at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel on July 30 before its departure from here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She said it was the highest honor and greatest happiness that she was received by Kim Jong Il and the troupe had a chance to perform in his presence, she gave her impressions of the performance tour as follows: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il spared time to appreciate our performance when it was on a local performance tour. All the members of the dancing troupe enthusiastically performed with boundless reverence for him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il gave precious instructions which would serve as guidelines for our dancing troupe's activities, saying that the song and dance "Small River" and other numbers are good pieces reflecting patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a Russian artiste I was deeply impressed to meet him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We got deep impressions when we visited Pyongyang Kim Won Gyun Conservatory and the Songdowon International Children's Camp. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Equipped with all educational facilities, the conservatory is a seat of learning music rare to be found in any other countries of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I pay tribute to Kim Jong Il who has such noble view on the younger generation as sparing nothing for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will become richer and more powerful in the future under his leadership.

Dismantlement of "UN Command" Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Civic and public organizations and political parties of south Korea including the preparatory committee of the Solidarity for Progress of south Korea, the Citizen's Solidarity for Democratic Society and the Democratic Labour Party reportedly held a meeting near the U.S. embassy in Seoul on July 27 at which they made public a declaration on behalf of 756 figures from all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "UN Command", an aggressive military mechanism of the U.S., should be dissolved in order to achieve peace on the Korean Peninsula, the declaration said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called for scrapping the aggressive south Korea-U.S. "alliance" which serves the U.S. interests only and all shackling "agreements" to support it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day members of civic and social organizations of south Korea including the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the Citizens' Solidarity for Democratic Society and the Solidarity for Social Progress in south Korea also held a seminar in Seoul on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of the conclusion of the Armistice Agreement and called on the people to turn out in the actions for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 10 civic and public organizations of south Korea called a joint press conference in front of the building of the "Ministry of National Defense", demanding the dissolution of the "UN Command" and the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea.

Cuban Charge d' Affaires a.i. Hosts Reception
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) --Enrique Montoto Cruz, charge d' affaires ad interim of the Cuban embassy in Pyongyang, Monday hosted a reception at the embassy on the 54th anniversary of the attack on the Moncada Barracks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea Choe Thae Bok, Minister of Foreign Trade Rim Kyong Man, Minister of Education Kim Yong Jin who is chairman of the Korea-Cuba Solidarity Committee, Acting Chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol, Vice-Minister of the People's Armed Forces Pak Jae Gyong, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Choe Su Hon, Vice-Chairman of the Korean Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission Son Kwang Ho and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cuban embassy officials were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Enrique Montoto Cruz in his speech said the friendly ties established under the deep concern of President Kim Il Sung, the great leader of the Korean people, and Supreme Commander of the Cuban Revolutionary Armed Forces Fidel Castro Ruz were constantly developing today in the struggle for defending socialism under the wise leadership of the supreme leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the belief that the Korean people would achieve bigger successes in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and accomplishment of the cause of the country's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok in his speech said the attack on the Moncada Barracks made by the Cuban revolutionaries under the command of Fidel Castro Ruz was a historical event that demonstrated the revolutionary will of the Cuban people to overthrow the pro-U.S. dictatorial regime and build a true sovereign and independent state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will value friendship with the Cuban people and make all their efforts to steadily strengthen it in the future, he declared.

U.S. Denounced for Sparking Global Arms Race
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- The United States is the world's biggest possessor of missiles and nukes and exposed to no military threat. It, however, is working more desperately to launch a new war of aggression, while speeding up its arms buildup, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The U.S. arms buildup is sparking a new arms race worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The policy of strength is the basic state policy of the U.S.  The arms buildup escalated by it under the pretext of coping with what it called a "new challenge" is aimed to beat its rivals and hold military supremacy. In other word, it is intended to realize its ambition to dominate the world by exercising high-handed military power. To this end, it is pushing ahead with the arms buildup and straining the situation under the signboard of coping with a "new threat" and "new challenge." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those countries with their sovereignty being exposed to the grave threat by the U.S. are channeling great efforts into bolstering their military power. If a country is to beat back U.S. aggression, it should have in place military means strong enough to cope with it. Many counties are, therefore, increasing investment in the field of national defence. Now dozens of countries are keen to have access to nukes worldwide. This fact alone clearly indicates that the U.S. arms buildup is sparking a new arms race, a nuclear arms race. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With nothing can the U.S. hide its true colors as a chieftain of the global arms race. The U.S. would be well advised to stop the adventurous arms buildup and moves to provoke a war swimming against the trend of the times.

Papers Hail Successful Election to Local Power Bodies
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Papers today editorially hail the successful holding of the election of the deputies to the provincial (municipality directly under central authority), city (district) and county people's assemblies of the DPRK amid high political enthusiasm of all people in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il participated in the election of deputies to the local power bodies together with farmers of the Chusang Co-op Farm in Hamju County, South Hamgyong Province, greatly encouraging the voters across the country, papers note, and go on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 99.82 percent of all the registered voters participated in voting and 100 percent of them voted for the candidates for deputies registered. This is a manifestation of the firm support and profound trust of all people in the socialist government in the DPRK under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says that this election fully demonstrated the firm confidence and will of the Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK people to eternally hold President Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the father of the nation and the eternal sun of Juche and bring about a decisive turn in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il and the might of the single-minded unity of the revolutionary ranks and advantages of the socialist system in the DPRK. This is the most shining success made by the election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The election strikingly demonstrated the fixed will of the people to defend and glorify the Korean-style socialism to the last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It helped lay a solid foundation for further increasing the function and role of the DPRK government as required by the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editorial calls for achieving a new leap forward in the drive for building a socialist economic power by maintaining an uninterrupted surge in the revolutionary spirit that has grown stronger through this election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is essential to thoroughly ensure the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il over the building of the government and its activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal exploits performed by Kim Jong Il in the building of the government in the course of the Songun revolution should be defended and glorified to the last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to give full play to the advantages of Korean-style socialism in all fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An all-out charge should be waged for the building of an economic power in the revolutionary soldier spirit and the spirit of Thaechon.

Rodong Sinmun on WPK's Songun Politics
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Songun politics pursued by the Workers' Party of Korea fully incorporates the steadfast faith in independence, stout-hearted grit, unswerving political decision and distinguished political ability of Kim Jong Il, says Rodong Sinmun in an article Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's high dignity and authority are immediately his unquestioned authority and all the victories and epoch-making changes are historical miracles wrought by his Songun politics, notes the author of the article, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has been throwing its rays as a dignified independent power century after century. This is unthinkable apart from Songun politics of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK's Songun politics is one resolutely safeguarding the sovereignty and dignity of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Regarding it as the paramount issue of principle for defending the supreme interests of the state and the basic interests of the revolution to safeguard the sovereignty and dignity of the country and the nation, this policy relentlessly strikes back any attempt to provoke or infringe upon the sovereignty and dignity of the DPRK, without the slightest concession and compromise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songun is, immediately, independence and dignity. It is owing to the great Songun politics that no one dares provoke the dignity of the DPRK and the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The WPK's Songun politics is the one solving all the problems arising in the revolution and construction in its own way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Basing itself on the principle of independence, the WPK decisively rejects the interference and pressure of any outsiders and resolves all the questions arising in the revolution and construction in its own way in conformity with the interests of the Korean revolution and the situation of the country, not wedded to any ready-made theory and formula. This is why the WPK's Songun politics is the most authoritative and viable politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK gives a steadfast continuity to independence in the external relations, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It resolves all the problems arising in external relations fairly and squarely in accordance with its opinion and will. In the international arena, the DPRK pushes through its intention, saying what it wants to say, neither reading other's face nor bound by any fetters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songun politics of the WPK is the most steadfast politics of independence which makes it possible to highly display the dignity of the nation and bring only brilliant victories.

Imperialists' Disintegration Strategy Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- The countries and peoples struggling for independence should clearly see through the reactionary nature and danger of the imperialists' moves to disorganize them from within and cope with these moves with sharp vigilance today when the imperialists are still persisting in them, urges Rodong Sinmun in a signed article Tuesday, which reads in part: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists are getting more desperate in their attempts to establish their domination over and commit looting in the anti-imperialist independent countries and those situated at strategic vantages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a hackneyed strategy of the imperialists to disintegrate the progressive countries from within. They run the whole gamut of means and ways to apply this strategy against the anti-imperialist independent countries. They resort to an extensive smear campaign and false propaganda against the political systems, policies and leadership of those countries which do not meekly obey them in an effort to whittle away confidence in the leadership. And they employ non-governmental organizations to give money to ideologically wavering people so they may blight society, violating the state law and orders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is typical of this strategy these days is to drive a wedge between political forces in order to divide them and set them at each other's throats. These maneuvers of the imperialists give rise to disputes between political forces and complicated situation in no small number of countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists also resort to the stratagem of sowing the seed of discord and creating antagonism between different nationalities, races and religious sects under one state system for their internal disintegration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There will be grave consequences if high vigilance is not maintained against the imperialists' moves to disorganize other countries from within and they are not thwarted in advance. Former socialist countries collapsed because their peoples were fooled by the imperialists' disintegration strategy.

Foreign Guests Arrive
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- Chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the Bulgarian National Assembly Solomon Passy and his party and a delegation of the Vietnam - DPRK Friendship Association headed by Pham Tat Dong who is the chairman of the Educational Panel of the State Council of Education arrived here Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also arriving here on the same day was the family of former Vice-Chairman of the China - Korea Friendship Association Gan Yetao.

Over 150 Cases of Aerial Espionage Committed against DPRK in July
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists and the south Korean forces committed more than 150 cases of aerial espionage against the DPRK in July by mobilizing strategic and tactical reconnaissance planes with different missions, according to a military source. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On July 30 a U-2 made a shuttle flight from the east to the west for a long time to perpetrate electronic reconnaissance and photographing of the overall area of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An overseas-based E-3 repeatedly flew in the air over south Korea to commit madcap aerial espionage against the targets in the depth of the DPRK from July 24 to 26, while commanding air corps involved in the exercises for close air support and support to the ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On July 5 and 18 an EP-3 was busy flying in the air above the east and west coasts of the DPRK to spy on the important targets of the DPRK along the forefront and seabed of the East and West seas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists and the south Korean forces flew several tactical reconnaissance planes almost every day to spy on the areas along the front and coastal areas of the DPRK. 8 planes were involved on July 13 and 6 on July 12 and 27 each and 5 on July 10 and 26 each.

Japanese Authorities' Suppression of Koreans in Japan under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- The Japanese authorities' suppression of Koreans is a grave racial discrimination and worst human rights abuse wantonly violating the major international human rights regulations including the UN Charter and the World Declaration of Human Rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A DPRK delegate said this addressing the plenary session of the UN General Assembly on July 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the issue related to the Japanese authorities' suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans in Japan has been brought for discussion at the UN, he re-clarified the DPRK's stand on the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the DPRK was compelled to propose discussing a supplementary item at the UN General Assembly at its final phase because the Japanese authorities' crackdown upon the Koreans in Japan and their organization has reached an intolerable reckless phase, he cited concrete facts to prove it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will use all media of the UN to continue accusing Japan till it ceases its politically motivated moves to destroy Chongryon and crack down upon the Koreans in Japan, regardless of what sort of resolution is produced by the session, he declared.

Kim Jong Il Inspects Sub-Unit of KPA
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 31 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected a sub-unit of KPA Unit 4318. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He acquainted himself with the sub-unit's performance of duty before looking round the outside and inside of the new barracks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round the cozy barracks and different facilities kept neat and tidy, he expressed great satisfaction over the successful construction of the modern barracks and extended thanks to the servicepersons who took part in it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that soldiers of the sub-unit built the barracks by their own efforts by actively tapping and using locally available materials, he said that it is the brilliant fruition of the spirit of self-reliance and noble patriotism displayed by the army of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took deep care of the soldiers' service and living, while making the rounds of the education room, bed-room, mess hall, wash-cum-bath house, non-staple food store, outdoor resting place, barn and greenhouse and other places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the commanding officers and soldiers of the sub-unit for having spruced up the inside and outside of the barracks and successfully built modern entertainment, educational and supply service facilities by their concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our army has brought a radical change not only in the ideological and moral traits and combat and political training but in all other fields including its appearance as regular forces and management of the unit in the great era of Songun, thus performing a vanguard role as the main driving force for the revolution, he said, adding that this precious exploit performed by the heroic KPA provides a sure guarantee for the victory of the Juche-oriented revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the sub-unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Hwang Pyong So and Kim Sung Yon, vice department directors of the WPK Central Committee.

Rodong Sinmun condena a EE.UU. por su carrera armamentista 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 31 de julio (ATCC) -- Aunque Estados Unidos es la primera potencia del mundo en el arsenal de armas nucleares y misiles y no esta sometido a ninguna amenaza militar, se enfrasca mas que nunca en el aumento armamentista y otros preparativos para desatar una nueva guerra de agresion, lo cual trae una nueva carrera armamentista a escala mundial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual de este martes y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La principal politica estatal de EE.UU. es la de garrote. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@A fin de tomar la hegemonia militar al aventajarse a sus rivales, el imperio acelera el aumento armamentista y agrava intencionalmente la situacion pretextando hacer frente a los "nuevos desafios y amenazas".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Es decir, quiere satisfacer su ambicion de dominar el mundo apelandose al despotismo militar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ahora, los paises con la soberania amenazada seriamente por EE.UU. encauzan mucha fuerza al fortalecimiento de las fuerzas armadas por la simple razon de que para detener la agresion norteamericana es preciso poseer los medios militares capaces de enfrentarla. Por eso, muchos paises aumentan la inversion en el sector de defensa nacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Actualmente, en el ambito mundial llegan a decenas los paises que tratan de poseer las armas nucleares. Este hecho demuestra que las maniobras de aumento armamentista de EE.UU. producen una nueva carrera armamentista, en particular, la nuclear. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  EE.UU. no podra encubrir de ninguna manera su naturaleza criminal de promotor de la carrera armamentista mundial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El debe abandonar su aventurero incremento armamentista y las maniobras de provocacion de guerra que contravienen a la corriente de la epoca.

Banquete por el 26 de Julio
